              "CBI_Flag": 0,
              "Description": "\nTHE BOAR'S HEAD HOLLAND MICHIGAN FACILITY IS EQUIPPED TO RESPOND TO ACCIDENTAL SPILLS OR RELEASES WITH A FULLY EQUIPPED AND TRAINED HAZMAT TEAM, THE TEAM MEMBERS HAVE ALL COMPLETED 40 HOURS OF TRAINING AND 8 HOURS OF REFRESHER TRAINING YEARLY, WE COORDINATE THESE RESPONSES WITH THE HOLLAND TOWNSHIP FIRE DEPARTMENT, AND CONDUCT REGULAR DRILLS FOR THE EMERGENCY RESPONSES. THE FACILITY IS EQUIPPED WITH AMMONIA DETECTORS IN CRITICAL AREAS \nOF THE PLANT THAT IN THE EVENT OF AN AMMONIA LEAK WILL SOUND ALARMS AND AUTOMATICALLY START EXHAUST FANS. THE COMPRESSOR ROOM IS EQUIPPED WITH AN AMMONIA ABSORBTION TANK THAT IN THE EVENT OF A SAFETY VALVE RELEASE OR FAILURE THE AMMONIA WILL NOT REACH ANY OFF SITE RECEPTORS AND BE CONTAINED WITHIN THE WATER TANK. THE OTTAWA COUNTY EMERGENCY SERVICES DEPARTMENT IS COORDINATED WITH THE SAFETY DEPARTMENT AND IN THE EVENT OF AN EMERGENCY \nSITUATION, THEY WILL IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE HOLLAND FIRE AND POLICE DEPARTMENTS, ALERT THE SURROUNDING COMMUNITY AS TO THE EXTENT OF THE RELEASE. BOAR'S HEAD HAS GONE TO EXTENSIVE LENGTHS TO PUT IN PLACE EXTRA SAFEGUARDS IN ORDER TO PROTECT THE SURROUNDING COMMUNITY FROM OFFSITE RELEASES. THE IMMEDIATE GOAL IN A SPECIFIC INCIDENT IS ASSURING THE SAFETY AND HEALTH OF BOAR'S HEAD EMPLOYEES AND RENDERING AID TO THOSE IN NEED. IT IS ALSO \nTHE GOAL OF THE BOAR'S HEAD HAZMAT TEAM TO CONTROL THE SITUATION AND CLEAN UP THE CONTAMINATED AREA BEFORE IT HARMS THE ENVIRONMENT OR THE SURROUNDING COMMINUNITY. IT IS THE PHILOSOPHY OF THE BOAR'S HEAD MANAGEMENT TEAM THAT WE WILL ONLY PRODUCE OUR PRODUCTS IF WE CAN DO IT SAFELY AND WITHOUT HARMING THE ENVIRONMENT.",
