      "SummaryText": "BOAR'S HEAD MAINTAINS THAT WE WILL UTILIZE THE BEST INSTALLATION STANDARDS AVAILABLE TO THE AMMONIA REFRIGERATION INDUSTRY, WE ARE MEMBERS OR THE IIAR AND STAY UP TO DATE ON THE LATEST TECHONOLOGY THAT IS USED IN OUR PROCESS (see attached ammonia refrigeration guidlines for details)\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThe Boar's Head management team recognizes that the safety and safety training of our \nassociates are paramount to an environment of productivity and well being of the \nassociates in our facilities as well as the surrounding community, we have on staff a \nfull time safety coordinator and a health care associate on all production shifts. We \nroutinely train all of the staff on process safety as well as lockout tagout, hazcom, \nand food safety. We have located ammonia detectors in all areas where there is a risk \nfor an ammonia leak, we have engineered in controls and a water absorbtion system in \nthe event of a multiple system failure, will contain any ammonia that would be \ndischarged through the relief valve vent lines. The training that we utilize for the \noperators of our ammonia refrigeration system consists of hands on, books and computer \nassisted training. We continuously monitor and audit our PSM system in order to prevent \nmechanical or operational failures of our system."
